                <li class="ActionBar-items-item"><a class="ActionLink gtm_share" data-platform="linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wamc.org%2Fnews%2F2021-08-17%2Fpresident-biden-stands-by-afghanistan-approach&mini=true&title=President%20Biden%20Stands%20By%20Afghanistan%20Approach&summary=President%20Biden%20returned%20to%20the%20White%20House%20Monday%20to%20address%20the%20nation%20after%20the%20Taliban%20ousted%20the%20Afghan%20government.%20The%20takeover%20sent%20thousands%20to%20Kabul%E2%80%99s%20airport%20seeking%20flights%20out%20of%20the%20country%2C%20leading%20to%20striking%20images%20of%20people%20clinging%20to%20American%20transport%20planes%20and%20several%20deaths.%20In%20his%20address%2C%20the%20president%20said%20he%20stands%20by%20his%20decision%20to%20pull%20out%20American%20troops%20after%20two%20decades.%20For%20analysis%20of%20the%20U.S.%20response%2C%20WAMC%E2%80%99s%20Jim%20Levulis%20spoke%20with%20Sarah%20Kreps%2C%20a%20former%20Air%20Force%20officer%20and%20a%20professor%20at%20Cornell%20University%20in%20the%20department%20of%20government.&source=WAMC"
    target="_blank" data-social-service="linkedin">
    <svg><use xlink:href="#mono-icon-linkedin"></use></svg><span>LinkedIn</span>
</a>
</li>
            
        
    </ul>
</ps-actionbar>

                            </div>
                        

                        
                            <div class="ArticlePage-bottomByline">
                                
    <div class="ArticlePage-authorInfo">
        
            <div class="ArticlePage-authorInfo-image">
                <a aria-label="Jim Levulis" href="https://www.wamc.org/people/jim-levulis">
                <img alt="" src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/b2e4361/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1600x2133+0+133/resize/150x200!/quality/90/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Flegacy%2Fsites%2Fwamc%2Ffiles%2F201701%2Fjim_levulis_headshot-01.jpg" srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/efe259e/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1600x2133+0+133/resize/300x400!/quality/90/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Flegacy%2Fsites%2Fwamc%2Ffiles%2F201701%2Fjim_levulis_headshot-01.jpg 2x" width="150" height="200">
                </a>
            </div>
        

        <div class="ArticlePage-authorInfo-bio">
            
                <div class="ArticlePage-authorInfo-bio-name">
                    <a href="https://www.wamc.org/people/jim-levulis" aria-label="">Jim Levulis</a>
                </div>
            

            <div class="ArticlePage-authorInfo-bio-content">
                
                    Born and raised in Eden, NY, Jim has been WAMC’s Associate News Director since October 2016. Since 2020, Jim has hosted WAMC's main news programs: Midday Magazine, Northeast Report and Northeast Report Late Edition. From 2013 to 2016, he worked as WAMC's Berkshire Bureau Chief for three years. Jim is also the producer of the podcast A New York Minute In History. He previously worked as a reporter, producer and anchor at WAER, an NPR member station in Syracuse. He has experience in Top 40 radio and has spent time with NPR member station WBFO and CBS-affiliate WIVB-TV, both in Buffalo.
                
            </div>

            <div class="ArticlePage-authorInfo-bio-cta">
                
                    <a href="https://www.wamc.org/people/jim-levulis" aria-label="See stories by Jim Levulis">
                        See stories by Jim Levulis
                    </a>
                
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

                                
